def: One who strives to put another under obligation; an officiousperson; hence, a flatterer. Used also adjectively.Smiling pickthanks, and base newsmongers. Shak.
The stipe when developed into an internode between calyx andcorolla, as in the Pink family. Gray.
The theory or practice of paternal government. See Paternalgovernment, under Paternal. London Times.
A soft, earthy substance, of a white, grayish, or yellowishwhite color, consisting of calcium carbonate, and having the samecomposition as common limestone.
A natural passage or canal; as, the external auditory meatus.See Illust. of Ear.

A large class of Echinodermata, including numerous extinctfamilies and genera, but comparatively few living ones. Most of thefossil species, like some that are recent, were attached by a jointedstem. See Blastoidea, Cystoidea, Comatula.
